00:45:00.109 --> 00:45:01.109
And then they don't do it.

00:45:01.109 --> 00:45:02.140
They didn't zero us out this year either.

00:45:02.140 --> 00:45:03.670
I mean, we were not cut at all.

00:45:03.670 --> 00:45:06.500
In fact, we should be cut out a little bit
compared to everything out there.

00:45:06.500 --> 00:45:11.310
I don't mean "should be," but we can expect
to be because everything is gonna be shrunk

00:45:11.310 --> 00:45:12.310
down a bit.

00:45:12.310 --> 00:45:18.470
But the big cut was in 1983 when Ronald Reagan,
in the early--.

00:45:18.470 --> 00:45:19.470
Ronald Reagan became President.

00:45:19.470 --> 00:45:23.550
He said we should not be paying for public
radio or TV.

00:45:23.550 --> 00:45:28.410
And so, he wanted to zero out the corporation
for public broadcasting, which is the umbrella

00:45:28.410 --> 00:45:29.410
group.

00:45:29.410 --> 00:45:31.220
And, in fact, he succeeded.

00:45:31.220 --> 00:45:32.680
The whole system changed.

00:45:32.680 --> 00:45:34.360
There was actually CPB funding.

00:45:34.360 --> 00:45:35.950
I don't know the exact amount.

00:45:35.950 --> 00:45:42.030
But it was most of the funding for NPR was
coming from the federal government in the

00:45:42.030 --> 00:45:43.290
'70s.

00:45:43.290 --> 00:45:48.210
And there was corporate and then, and when
Reagan came in, he made good on "we're not

00:45:48.210 --> 00:45:49.210
gonna fund you directly."

00:45:49.210 --> 00:45:53.430
And, but what happened was the system changed,
so they--.

00:45:53.430 --> 00:45:55.980
The CPB money now goes to the stations.

00:45:55.980 --> 00:46:01.400
And stations get about 15 percent on average
of what they need to run their stations from

00:46:01.400 --> 00:46:02.400
the CPB.

00:46:02.400 --> 00:46:05.079
And then, some percentage of money comes to
us.

00:46:05.079 --> 00:46:06.850
So, one of the, comes to NPR.

00:46:06.850 --> 00:46:15.050
Well, they have to buy NPR shows because if
they didn't run NPR shows, they'd make less

00:46:15.050 --> 00:46:18.310
money from listeners because listeners tune
in to hear NPR shows.

00:46:18.310 --> 00:46:19.940
I mean, it's a simple dynamic.

00:46:19.940 --> 00:46:23.520
So, it's a good deal all around.

00:46:23.520 --> 00:46:30.270
